<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 17-year-old boy has drowned at a beach near Port Macquarie in New South Wales. </p>

<p>The boy got into difficulties while swimming with his family at Diamond Head, about 40km south of Port Macquarie, at about 1pm on Wednesday.</p>

<p>Police officers pulled him from the water and started CPR, before paramedics arrived and took over. </p>

<p>Sadly, he died at the scene.</p>

<p>A report will be prepared for the coroner. </p>
